"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147445","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-19","<p>The Northern Ireland Executive, like the devolved administrations in Scotland and Wales, is expected to meet the costs of public sector pensions and spending on health and education from within its existing budgets.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-11-19T13:52:44.437Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147445/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147445/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147445/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Public Expenditure: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will give further financial assistance to the Northern Ireland Executive to fund public sector pensions, health and education.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","214159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147446","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-17","<p><strong>The Treasury have made no assessment of the potential effects on the British economy of a closure of the Suez Canal to shipping.</strong></p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-11-17T10:05:56.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147446/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147446/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147446/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Shipping: Suez","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what contingency assessment his Department has made of the potential effects on the British economy of a closure of the Suez Canal to shipping.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","214108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147447","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>The Government is supportive of credit unions and has taken a number of steps to assist them, most recently including:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Investing up to £38 million in an expansion project for credit unions, aimed at helping credit unions expand and grow sustainably</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li>Issuing a Call for Evidence on credit unions, to which the Government will respond shortly.</li><li>Removing unnecessary restrictions on credit unions via the Legislative Reform Order that came into effect in January 2012.</li><li>These measures will help increase the capability of the credit union sector allowing it to become a viable option for financial services provision for an even wider range of consumers.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is concerned about consumer detriment in the payday market and believes the FCA’s new, more robust regulatory system will help to improve protections for consumers who still choose to use pay day lenders.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-11-20T17:49:06.127Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147447/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147447/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147447/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will take steps to encourage saving through credit unions as a means of preventing poverty and payday loans.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","214140"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147448","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer by my noble friend, Lord Freud, of 19 March 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, House of Lords, Column WA31, and also the answers of 3 March 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, House of Lords, Columns WA278-279.</p><p> </p><p>On 10 October, the Government published a consultation paper on local welfare support which outlines the Government’s policy stance on this issue; a copy of which is attached.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-11-17T16:22:41.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147448/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147448/answer","PQ 214073 Consultation Document.pdf","Consultation Paper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147448/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-10","Welfare Assistance Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether he informed local authorities prior to the publication of the provisional local government finance settlement that dedicated funding for local welfare assistance schemes would no longer be available from April 2015.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","214073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147449","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-17","<p>An environmental impact assessment is required for development proposals which are likely to have a significant impact on the environment. The procedure for establishing whether an environmental impact assessment is necessary (the screening process) is set out in planning regulations and explained in planning guidance (<a href="http://planningguidance.planningportal.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://planningguidance.planningportal.gov.uk/</a>).</p><p>The guidance makes it clear that only a very small proportion of developments should require a formal environmental impact assessment. We have consulted on proposals to reduce the number of residential cases that local planning authorities have to screen (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/339528/Technical_consultation_on_planning.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/339528/Technical_consultation_on_planning.pdf )</a> and we will publish the Government's response in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-11-17T16:34:24.72Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147449/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147449/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147449/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-10","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, under what circumstances an environmental impact assessment can be requested when a housing development is proposed; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","Faversham and Mid Kent","Sir Hugh Robertson","214064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147450","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-20","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2014-11-20T15:29:45.587Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147450/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147450/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147450/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-10","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of houses under local development plans are (a) private and (b) social housing.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","213947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147451","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Government are consulting on a range of options for how local welfare provision should be funded in 2015/16. A copy of the consultation is attached.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-11-17T17:04:29.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147451/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147451/answer","PQ 213988 Consultation Document.pdf","Consultation Document","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147451/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-10","Welfare Assistance Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department has issued to local authorities on supporting the most vulnerable residents when the local welfare assistance schemes end in April 2015.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","213988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147452","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-11-20","<p>There have been no contracts signed by my Department since 2010 which have been cancelled with such a clause attached to the contract.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-11-20T16:06:03.207Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147452/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147452/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147452/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-11-10","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many contracts signed by his Department with suppliers of services or consultants include a clause providing that if the contract is abrogated by the Government, the provider or consultant will be compensated for lost income since 2010.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","214002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147453","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-17","<p>Since 2010 DCMS have signed no contracts with suppliers of services or consultants which include such a clause.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-11-17T17:05:05.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147453/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147453/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147453/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-10","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many contracts signed by his Department with suppliers of services or consultants include a clause providing that if the contract is abrogated by the Government, the provider or consultant will be compensated for lost income since 2010.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","214003"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147454","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Government is committed to the policy of free admission to the permanent collections of the museums and galleries sponsored by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport, which is a condition of grant-in-aid. The Government has limited reductions in funding for national museums in order to maintain free entry, and to protect their world-class collections and front-line services.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-11-17T17:06:30.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147454/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147454/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147454/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-10","Museums and Galleries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to support free entry to museums and galleries; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","213980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147455","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-17","<p>DCMS is working with the Government Property Unit to assess the current use of Blythe House as the Government seeks to provide a long term, cost effective solution for museum storage and conservation facilities, as well as to improve access to the national collections. Property valuation information is however commercially sensitive and any disclosure would adversely affect the Government’s future ability to negotiate efficiencies and achieve value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-11-17T17:07:00.523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147455/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147455/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147455/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-10","Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the freehold value of Blythe House is.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","213971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147456","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-18","<p>The Telecommunications Consumer Action Plan has made strong progress. To continue important work on this issue I have invited the major Mobile Network Operators to a Round Table meeting, where the MNOs will confirm details of the liability caps they will offer for any unauthorised use of lost or stolen phones.</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-11-18T17:20:35.593Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147456/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147456/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147456/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-10","Mobile Phones: Theft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, with reference to his Department's announcement of 3 December 2013, on putting an end to shock mobile telephone bills, what progress his Department has made on implementing a consumer liability cap on stolen mobile telephones.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","214036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147457","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Government has been in discussions with stakeholders on tackling partial not-spots since the Spring. The current consultation will build on those discussions and give a wide range of people, and organisations, a reasonable opportunity to comment on the Government’s proposed options.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-11-17T16:34:56.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147457/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147457/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147457/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-10","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the decision-making process was for setting the duration of his Department's consultation Tackling partial not-spots in mobile phone coverage, published on 5 November 2014; and whether different durations were considered during the consultation planning stage.","false","Biography information for Iain McKenzie","Inverclyde","Iain McKenzie","214047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147458","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-17","<p>DCMS has not sold any buildings between 2010 and 2014.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-11-17T17:05:59.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147458/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147458/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147458/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-10","Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many buildings his Department sold in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013 and (e) 2014.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","213996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147459","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-18","<p>This Government is dedicated to continuing the implementation of this report.</p><p>I continue to press the football authorities for improvements in their governance of the sport, however significant improvements have been made. For example, the FA Board now meets Sport England governance requirements. Both the Premier League and The FA are providing funding to the supporter groups, including the Football Supporters Federation and Supporters Direct. All Premier League and Football League clubs are now required to have a designated Supporter Liaison Officer and Financial Fair Play rules. These requirements aim to improve financial stability and management across the Leagues. The Expert Group on barriers to supporter ownership and engagement, were proposed by Supporters Direct, and recently launched on 21 October.</p><p>Following the 2012 Downing Street summit on racism in football, The FA are also now delivering against a whole sport Inclusion and Anti-Discrimination Plan called “Football’s for Everyone”. This plan seeks to build equality and inclusion in football.</p><p>Lastly, I am also pleased to note that the FA Inclusion Advisory Board reports quarterly to DCMS on their progress.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-11-18T14:32:37.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147459/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147459/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147459/answer","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147459/answer/previousversion/28346","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-10","Football","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department has taken to implement the conclusions and recommendations of the Culture, Media and Sport Committee's Seventh Report of Session 2010-12, HC 792-I, on football governance; and what further such steps it plans to take.","false","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","Faversham and Mid Kent","Sir Hugh Robertson","214065"
