"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147515","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-11-20","As I stated to the House during Oral Questions to the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs on 28 October 2014, Official Report, column 153, the Government has received this invitation and is considering whether to attend the Conference, and will update the House once we have reached a decision.","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-11-20T14:56:21.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147515/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147515/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147515/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-11-10","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government will be represented at the conference on the Humanitarian Consequences of Nuclear Weapons taking place in Vienna in December 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","214115"
