"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143363","Department of Health","false","2014-11-17","<p>Health and Wellbeing Boards (HWBs) have been in place in every upper tier and unitary local authority since April 2013. In that time, the Department has implemented a range of programme support, direct engagement and evaluation, in order to maintain an ongoing overview of the development and effectiveness of HWBs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department has funded the Local Government Association (LGA) to deliver a development and improvement programme for local health and wellbeing systems, with a strong focus on supporting HWBs’ development. An independent evaluation of both the programme and the current state of development and effectiveness of HWBs was published in April 2014. This can be found on the LGA website at the following link. A further independent evaluation is due for publication in December this year.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong><a href="http://www.local.gov.uk/documents/10180/11493/Great+expectations+-+A+review+of+the+Health+and+Wellbeing+System+Improvement+Programme/d8c4b00e-c3fc-4598-9e87-e5a719df2274" target="_blank">www.local.gov.uk/documents/10180/11493/Great+expectations+-+A+review+of+the+Health+and+Wellbeing+System+Improvement+Programme/d8c4b00e-c3fc-4598-9e87-e5a719df2274</a></strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Departmental officials have also reviewed independent evaluation, notably the King’s Fund study <em>Health and Wellbeing Boards: One Year On</em> published in October 2013; and the published reports of the intensive peer challenge visits delivered in local authorities as part of the LGA development programme.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-11-17T16:57:22.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143363/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143363/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143363/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-11-07","Health and Wellbeing Boards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of Health and Wellbeing Boards since their introduction.","false","Biography information for Mr David Ward","Bradford East","Mr David Ward","213831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143364","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-11-17","<p>World class broadband coverage across the UK is a priority for this Government. Funding for all local projects, including the Wales project has been allocated to achieve maximum coverage and value for money from the public investment.</p><p>At the end of September 2014 276,320 premises had been reached.</p><p>The Superfast Cymru project is set to achieve 93% superfast broadband coverage by the end of 2017.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-11-17T17:08:06.633Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143364/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143364/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143364/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-11-07","Broadband: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 17 June 2014 to Question 200020, what reports he has received of political bias in the prioritisation of the broadband rollout programme in Wales; if he will hold discussions with the Welsh Government on this matter; and if he will ensure that all areas in Wales benefit equally from the broadband rollout programme.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","213845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143365","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the Minister for Defence Equipment, Support and Technology (Philip Dunne) on 11 November 2014 to Question UIN 213403, to the hon. Member for North Durham (Kevan Jones).</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-17T16:48:59.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143365/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143365/answer","HOC 213403 Hansard Extract 11 November 2014.doc","Hansard Extract 11 November 2014.","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143365/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the timetable is for the training of Libyan troops in the UK: and when he expects that training to end.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143366","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my right hon. Friend the Minister of State for the Armed Forces (Mark Francois) on 28 October 2014, to Question UIN 210756.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-17T17:14:12.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143366/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143366/answer","HOC210756.doc","Hanard Extract 28 October 2014.","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143366/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many crew will be required to fully operate each of the two Queen Elizabeth-class aircraft carriers.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143367","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-18","<p>I receive regular written representations from right hon. and hon. Members, Trade Unions and others on this issue.</p><p>I have this year met the Prospect and Unite unions to discuss the normal pension age of the Defence Fire and Rescue Service. The issue was also raised at the Defence Whitley committee which I chaired in May and during my visit to the Defence Fire Training and Development Centre at Manston.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-11-18T17:37:54.773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143367/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143367/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143367/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Fire Services: Retirement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what representations he has received on the retirement age of his Department's firefighters; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143368","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Lightning II Joint Strike Fighter Program Office has reached an agreement in principle with Lockheed Martin to procure the next four F-35B aircraft for the UK. It is anticipated that the contract will be finalised in the near future, with aircraft deliveries scheduled to commence from mid 2016.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-17T17:13:43.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143368/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143368/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143368/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress has been made with the F-35 Lightning II order; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143369","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>Two hundred and twenty eight Libyan General Purpose Force personnel completed their training.</p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-17T16:48:25.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143369/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143369/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143369/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many of the Libyan service personnel who have received training in the UK since the start of this summer have completed the programme.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143370","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>Reservists may be called up for any task for which a Regular may be used, such as resilience and security activities, recent examples including supporting the flooding effort whereby Reservists assisted during civil contingencies particularly with logistic support and building of defences. More recently Reservists were used during the Commonwealth Games to fulfil Venue Security roles.</p><p>The Reserves Forces Act 1996 also allows for Reservists to be deployed in permanent service under the provisions of the Act (and amended under the Defence Reform Act 2014) if deemed necessary including activities and operations in the UK and Overseas. Reservists have provided formed companies for duties in Cyprus and will also provide a formed platoon for the next rotation in Afghanistan, and work is under way to mobilise medical practitioners to assist with Ebola in Sierra Leone.</p><p>There is a statutory obligation to report to Parliament when a call out order is made.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2014-11-17T17:19:47.463Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143370/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143370/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143370/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Reserve Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the role of the Reserves is (a) in dealing with civil contingencies and (b) generally; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143371","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-25","<p>UK Armed Forces continue to make a significant contribution to the international effort to counter ISIL. UK air assets remain active, conducting surveillance in Syria and surveillance and strike missions in Iraq. Through the action we have already taken, we are helping to halt and reverse ISIL's advances.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-25T16:50:48.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143371/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143371/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143371/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143371/answer/previousversion/28829","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress the surveillance mission in Syria has made; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143372","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-21","<p>The additional costs of the recent training programme for Libyan Armed Forces personnel is given in the attached table:</p><p> </p><p>The Libyan government has agreed to reimburse the Ministry of Defence for these costs. They have already paid £2.5 million, and we will continue to negotiate with them over paying the balance.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, small numbers of Libyan Armed Forces have been trained in UK staff colleges over the last three years and in Libya by the Defence Advisory Team. These activities cost approximately £0.5 million in financial year (FY) 2012-13 and approximately £1.7 million in FY 2013-14. The forecast for this activity in FY 2014-15 is £0.2 million.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","213247 ; 213248 ; 213336 ; 213337 ; 213404 ; 214166","2014-11-21T11:01:30.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143372/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143372/answer","213404 - Costs to UK for Training of Libyan Service Personnel.doc","Costs to UK of Training Libyan Service Personnel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143372/answer","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143372/answer/previousversion/28828","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost was of the recent training operations for Libyan soldiers.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143373","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-18","<p>From 1 January to 10 November 2014, the total number of RAF missions flown in Iraq by all UK military aircraft is 251.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-18T17:37:29.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143373/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143373/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143373/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many missions the RAF has flown in 2014 to date in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143374","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-19","<p>Airstrikes in Iraq, including those conducted by the RAF, have contributed directly to halting some of ISIL's advances, and supporting Iraqi forces engaged on the ground. We routinely assess the results of each strike conducted by UK aircraft, and the overall effect of strikes, including through the use of our surveillance assets, which we have deployed to improve the coalition's understanding of the situation on the ground.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-19T17:51:46.227Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143374/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143374/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143374/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of airstrikes in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143375","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>As previously announced, the base port for the Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers is Her Majesty's Naval Base Portsmouth.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-17T17:13:07.963Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143375/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143375/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143375/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the basing plans for the Queen Elizabeth-class aircraft carriers are; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143376","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-19","<p>In the last two years training on the unarmed HERMES 450 Unmanned Aircraft System has been conducted by Army personnel in Israel on a regular basis. The last training took place in July 2014. This training was a mixture of individual and pre-deployment training for HERMES operators, and technical training for support personnel. Over this period, more than 270 personnel received training by the civilian contractor in Israel. No training has been conducted within the Occupied Palestinian territories.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-19T17:52:21.583Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143376/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143376/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143376/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for which periods officers in the armed forces have been trained on the operation and use of drone technology in Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories in the last two years.","true","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","213867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143377","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-17","<p>The annual cost of a Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carrier's ship's company, based on a planned normal operating complement of 672 at 2014 capitation rates, is £34.6 million. This includes the additional tri-Service Longer Separation Allowance, based on the Royal Navy's normal operating cycle of 660 days at sea over three years.</p><p>Aircraft costs are attributed by aircraft type not by basing factors. The operational and other costs for embarked aircraft cannot therefore be separated by land or sea-based operation.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-17T17:12:24.847Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143377/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143377/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143377/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) operational and (b) other costs are for (i) crew and (ii) aircraft on each of the Queen Elizabeth-class aircraft carriers.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143378","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-18","<p>The Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) aircraft carriers will have the capacity to operate up to 36 Lightning II aircraft and four helicopters fitted with AEW radar. The QEC aircraft carriers are extremely versatile platforms and the precise mix of aircraft deployed will depend on the type of mission being undertaken. Operations in the littoral, for example, may require embarkation of more helicopters and fewer fast jets.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-11-18T17:41:53.047Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143378/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143378/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143378/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many F-35 Lightning II aircraft are intended to operate on each of the Queen Elizabeth-class aircraft carriers.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143379","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-11-19","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the Minister for Defence Equipment, Support and Technology (Philip Dunne) on 11 November 2014 to Question UIN 213403, to the hon. Member for North Durham (Kevan Jones).</p><p> </p><p>http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=213403</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-11-19T17:12:22.077Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143379/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143379/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143379/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-11-07","Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department's policy is on the future training of Libyan soldiers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vernon Coaker","Gedling","Vernon Coaker","213855"
