"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143424","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Department for Transport does not collect information on such flights.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All General Aviation flights are required to submit advance information, in the form of a General Aviation Report (GAR) prior to arriving in the UK. This information – including passenger details, flight details and aircraft details – is checked against Home Office IT systems.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All flights must also submit a flight plan before arriving in the UK to NATS (formally known as the National Air Traffic System). Border Force routinely cross references this data with GARs received.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Border Force risk assess all flights which are notified and seek to attend to all high priority flights.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","213912 ; 213914","2014-11-17T17:20:36.717Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143424/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143424/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143424/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-07","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many private flights have submitted flight plans to National Air Traffic Services in the last four years.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","213913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143425","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Department for Transport does not collect information on such flights.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All General Aviation flights are required to submit advance information, in the form of a General Aviation Report (GAR) prior to arriving in the UK. This information – including passenger details, flight details and aircraft details – is checked against Home Office IT systems.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All flights must also submit a flight plan before arriving in the UK to NATS (formally known as the National Air Traffic System). Border Force routinely cross references this data with GARs received.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Border Force risk assess all flights which are notified and seek to attend to all high priority flights.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","213912 ; 213913","2014-11-17T17:20:36.883Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143425/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143425/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143425/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-07","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many non-scheduled departures from the UK there have been by private aircraft since 2010.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","213914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143426","Home Office","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Home Office does not hold data on the number of private flights which have submitted general aviation reports on arrival rather than in advance. Border Force has the capability to identify flights which have not submitted Advance Passenger Information (API), which informs part of the risk assessment process. Where a flight does not submit API it will automatically be classified asHigh Priority, and will likely be met by a Border Force Officer.<br><br><br>The other requested data is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","213916","2014-11-17T16:35:51.01Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143426/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143426/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/143426/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-11-07","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many private flights have submitted general aviation reports upon arrival rather than in advance in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Mr Gordon Marsden","213915"
